cs.IT, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.MS, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with the analysis of channels in classical information theory using probability theory, monads, and domain theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses topology and capacity of channels, which suggests the sub-categories cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of domain theory and compact convex sets points towards cs.MS (Mathematical Software) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
